    "instruction": "Load metric.csv. For the following groups only: \n- ts-travel-service: kpi_name in ['workload','mem','socket','latency-50','latency-90','error']\n- ts-auth-service: kpi_name in ['cpu','socket','diskio','latency-50']\nFirst, compute each group's global p95 and p5 using the group's full available series (no time filtering). Then filter rows to the incident window 2024-01-24 09:34:39 UTC through 2024-01-24 10:04:39 UTC (inclusive). Identify anomaly rows where value >= p95 OR value <= p5. For each group produce a compact summary row with these fields: cmdb_id, kpi_name, global_count, p95, p5, total_anomalies_in_window, num_consecutive_sequences, longest_sequence_length_minutes, earliest_sequence_start_utc (ISO string), sample_anomalies (a short semicolon-separated list of up to 5 example pairs formatted as '(timestamp_ISO, value)'). Define consecutive sequences by timestamps that are adjacent minutes (difference exactly 60 seconds between successive anomaly timestamps). Return one summary row per group (limit to these groups only). Sort results by total_anomalies_in_window descending. Keep outputs compact and text-only."
}

